decks.notes: The main idea of this deck is to quickly fill up the graveyard with cards like Stinkweed Imp, Golgari Thug, and Golgari Grave-Troll, while utilizing cards like Bazaar of Baghdad and Serum Powder to help dredge through the deck. This allows the player to bring back powerful creatures like Ichorid and Prized Amalgam from the graveyard, creating a powerful board presence. The deck also includes disruptive cards like Force of Will and Mindbreak Trap to protect the combo and counter opponent's plays, making it a strong and fast-paced combo deck in a Vintage 1 vs 1 format.

The deck focuses on generating mana quickly and efficiently through cards like Grim Monolith and Tolarian Academy, along with mana artifacts like Black Lotus and Moxen. The goal is to assemble the Time Vault and Voltaic Key combo to take extra turns, while also utilizing Paradoxical Outcome to draw cards and generate even more mana. With the ability to disrupt opponents with Force of Will and other control elements, the deck aims to execute its combo quickly and overwhelm the opponent before they have a chance to respond.

This deck aims to use Underworld Breach to repeatedly cast powerful spells from the graveyard, combining fast mana, card draw, and disruption to assemble a combo win condition. The deck includes tutors like Demonic Tutor and Vampiric Tutor to find key pieces quickly, as well as powerful cards like Ancestral Recall, Time Walk, and Tinker. Force of Will and Hullbreacher provide disruption while cards like Ponder and Brainstorm help to dig for combo pieces. The deck is designed to be fast and explosive, aiming to win the game quickly through powerful combos.

The deck focuses on using hatebears and aggro creatures to disrupt the opponent's game plan while applying pressure with efficient creatures. It uses mana acceleration and disruptive elements like Chancellor of the Annex and Archon of Emeria to slow down the opponent, while also utilizing powerful cards like Anointed Peacekeeper and Seasoned Dungeoneer to control the board. The deck also includes hate cards like Chalice of the Void and Wasteland to further disrupt the opponent's strategy. Overall, the deck aims to overwhelm the opponent quickly while keeping them off balance with disruptive elements.
